7 Body with 19 segments, paraterga 2 rather well developed, but subsequent ones mostly represented by lateral swellings. Collum still large, covering the head from above, with 4-5 transverse rows of setigerous tubercles or pits. Following paraterga with three rows of similar tubercles or pits. Gonopods with poorly setose gonocoxae and a considerably shortened prefemoral+femoral (= setose) part, deeply biramous thereafter, with a long and flagelliform solenomere devoid of hairpad (
